The '''Pine Middle School shooting''' was a [[school shooting]] that occurred in [[Reno, Nevada]], [[United States]] on March 14, 2006.<ref name="FoxNews">{{cite news
 | title = Two Hurt in Reno Middle School Shooting
 | curly = y 
 | url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,187860,00.html
 | agency = [[Associated Press]]
 | work = 
 | publisher = [[Fox News Channel]]
 | location = [[New York City]], [[United States]]
 | date = 2006-03-14
 | accessdate = 2008-11-21
 | quote = An eighth-grader opened fire with a pistol Tuesday outside his middle school cafeteria, injuring two classmates, authorities said.
 }}</ref> The shooting was perpetrated by then fourteen-year-old student James Scott Newman who shot and injured two 14-year-old eighth grade classmates with a [[pistol]] that had belonged to his parents.<ref name="FoxNews" /><ref name="KOLOTV">{{cite news
 | first = Koula
 | last = Gianulias
 | coauthors = Kara Tsuboi, Ed Pearce
 | title = Reno School Shooting Team Report
 | curly = y 
 | url = http://www.kolotv.com/home/headlines/2461261.html
 | work = 
 | publisher = [[KOLO-TV]]
 | location = [[Reno, Nevada]], [[United States|USA]]
 | accessdate = 2008-11-21
 }}</ref>  Newman was arrested and charged as an adult on charges of attempted murder, use of a deadly weapon and use of a firearm by a minor but later plead guilty to different charges of two counts of [[Battery (crime)|battery]] with a deadly weapon, in which he had received sentencing as a [[juvenile (law)|juvenile]]. James Newman was sentenced to [[house arrest]] until he completed 200 hours of [[community service]].<ref name="WashingtonPost">{{cite news
 | first = Scott
 | last = Sonner
 | title = Teen Gets House Arrest in Nev. Shooting
 | curly = y 
 | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/05/26/AR2006052602039_Technorati.html
 | work = [[The Washington Post]]
 | publisher = [[Katharine Weymouth]]
 | location = [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States|USA]]
 | date = 2006-05-26
 | accessdate = 2008-11-21
 | quote = A 14-year-old boy who shot and injured two fellow middle school students was sentenced Friday to house arrest until he completes 200 hours of community service.
 }}</ref>

On March 25, 2008, athletics teacher Jencie Fagan, who was hailed a hero for her confrontation with the shooter, was selected as one of the three national winners for the Above & Beyond Citizen Honor from the Congressional Medal of Honor Society at a ceremony in [[Washington D.C.]]

== Background ==
Edward L. Pine Middle School is a Washoe County School District [[junior high school]] located at 4800 Neil Road, in Southern Reno.<ref name="pinemiddle">{{cite news
